headline: General Mills Balances High Protein Cereal Expansion With Recall Risks
summary: General Mills (NYSE:GIS) is entering the high protein cereal category through a new collaboration with GHOST. The company has also expanded a recall of certain Pillsbury Pizza Pops in Canada due to potential E. coli contamination. These developments highlight both product expansion in better for you cereals and operational risk in frozen snacks. headline: Is General Mills (GIS) Now A Value Opportunity After Recent Share Price Rebound?
summary: If you are wondering whether General Mills is a bargain or a value trap at around US$48.37 per share, you will want to see how its current price stacks up against a few different valuation checks. The stock has recently shown short term strength, with returns of 8.9% over the past week, 10.3% over the past month, and 5.8% year to date. headline: Post Holdings names former General Mills exec to lead its cereal, pet food business
summary: The CPG veteran will take over in April for Nicolas Catoggio, who recently became the company’s chief operating officer.
